{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a84ffa6-1f06-477e-815e-81d9f9e9dc8f","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. None of my specialized skills cover dump **analysis** (only collection), but here's what you can do:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, easiest)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\n   dotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n   ```\n   Key SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` (`printexception`) — print the last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary (for OOM crashes)\n   - `threads` — list all managed threads\n   - `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n2. **WinDbg + SOS** (Windows, most powerful)\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n\n### Quick triage workflow\n```\n> dotnet-dump analyze crash.dmp\n$ pe                   # check for an unhandled exception\n$ threads              # find the faulting thread\n$ setthread <id>\n$ clrstack             # see the managed stack trace\n$ clrstack -a          # include local variables\n```\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and analyze the file here? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79c3799b-951b-4bc3-b586-ed1508748b9d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me look at what tools and skills are available to help with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\n\nNone of these are designed for analyzing an existing .dmp file. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing .NET crash dumps using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze` on Linux, WinDbg with SOS on Windows, or lldb with SOS on macOS. I'll need to ask where their dump file is located and whether `dotnet-dump` is installed on their system.","outputTokens":668,"requestId":"A0C2:180EFF:957287:B899DD:6A013827"},"id":"63e7eac6-ca30-4b63-b132-2774030c941d","timestamp":"2026-05-11T02:00:24.396Z","parentId":"7d121e71-ba09-4a75-9916-2f764607df7f"}
